+          "text": "The final strongest biological subgroup in the dataset is the `dependency_KIF18A` subgroup defined by `lineage=colorectal`, `apc_mutation=1`, high `wnt_activity_score`, and `smad4_loss=0`, because it has the largest signed negative effect among the systematic subgroup tests.",
+          "kind": "refined"
+        }
+      ],
+      "analyses": [
+        {
+          "hypothesis_ids": ["h34"],
+          "code": "Adjusted growth coefficients from OLS models for POLR2A, TMED10, and DHX9.",
+          "result_summary": "Growth had negative adjusted coefficients for `dependency_POLR2A` (beta=-0.3053), `dependency_TMED10` (beta=-0.1010), and `dependency_DHX9` (beta=-0.1069), supporting a broad proliferation/screen-quality axis.",
+          "p_value": 1e-300,
+          "effect_estimate": -0.3052568827686115,
+          "significant": true
+        },
+        {
+          "hypothesis_ids": ["h35"],
+          "code": "Compare signed effects from the final systematic subgroup search across outcomes.",
+          "result_summary": "The KIF18A colorectal/APC/high-WNT/SMAD4-intact subgroup had the largest negative subgroup effect observed (mean difference=-1.0460), much larger than the canonical driver effects for BRAF, EGFR, ERBB2, KRAS, or RIT1.",
+          "p_value": 1e-300,
+          "effect_estimate": -1.045960332729322,
+          "significant": true
+        }
+      ]
+    }
+  ]
+}

diff --git a/example_data_depmap/tasks/depmap/named/analysis_summary.txt b/example_data_depmap/tasks/depmap/named/analysis_summary.txt
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..0795b31876dc6d720a9e381b821ac7182746f25f
--- /dev/null
+++ b/example_data_depmap/tasks/depmap/named/analysis_summary.txt
@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@
+Dataset ds001_depmap contains 50000 cell-line records with 10 CRISPR dependency outcomes. I analyzed binary molecular features, categorical lineage/culture/batch variables, continuous molecular scores, and screen covariates. Dependency scores are interpreted on their natural scale, where more negative values mean stronger dependency.
+
+Canonical driver dependencies were strongly recovered. `braf_v600e=1` predicted more negative `dependency_BRAF` (adjusted beta -0.5544; unadjusted means -0.8047 vs -0.2495, p approximately 1e-300). `egfr_amplification=1` predicted more negative `dependency_EGFR` (adjusted beta -0.3487; means -0.6010 vs -0.2524, p approximately 1e-300). `erbb2_amplification=1` predicted more negative `dependency_ERBB2` (adjusted beta -0.4325; means -0.6856 vs -0.2535, p approximately 1e-300). `kras_mutation=1` predicted more negative `dependency_KRAS` (adjusted beta -0.3088; means -0.5594 vs -0.2520, p approximately 1e-300).
+
+Several lineage signals seen in the first scan were explained by driver enrichment rather than independent lineage biology. `lineage=skin` was no longer associated with `dependency_BRAF` after adjustment for `braf_v600e` (beta -0.0021, p=0.706). `lineage=brain` was null for `dependency_EGFR` after adjustment for `egfr_amplification` (beta 0.0029, p=0.635). `lineage=breast` and `lineage=gastric` were null in the adjusted ERBB2 model. The `kras_mutation` by `lineage=pancreatic` interaction was also null (beta -0.0004, p=0.971), supporting KRAS mutation itself rather than a pancreatic-specific KRAS-mutant dependency.
+
+For RAS-pathway heterogeneity, `nf1_loss=1` was the clear RIT1-associated subgroup. `nf1_loss` lines had more negative `dependency_RIT1` scores than other lines (means -0.3527 vs -0.2572), and the association persisted after adjustment for growth and Cas9 activity (beta -0.0953, p approximately 1e-300).
+
+The strongest noncanonical pattern was for `dependency_KIF18A`. Main-effect scans identified `lineage=colorectal`, `apc_mutation=1`, high `wnt_activity_score`, and high `rnaseq_ASCL2_log2_tpm` as related signals. Refinement showed that the complete dependency subgroup was `lineage=colorectal`, `apc_mutation=1`, high `wnt_activity_score` (`>=0.819`), and `smad4_loss=0`. This subgroup had mean `dependency_KIF18A` -1.2990 versus -0.2530 in all other lines (effect -1.0460, p approximately 1e-300). Within colorectal/APC/high-WNT lines, `smad4_loss=0` had mean -1.2990 while `smad4_loss=1` had mean -0.2557 (effect -1.0433, p approximately 1e-300), indicating that SMAD4 loss suppresses the otherwise strong KIF18A dependency.
+
+MYC and chromosome 8q24 signals separated by outcome. Higher `rnaseq_MYC_log2_tpm` independently predicted more negative `dependency_DHX9` (adjusted beta -0.0160, p approximately 1e-300), while `myc_amplification` itself was not independent after MYC expression was included. For `dependency_RPL11`, high `copy_number_8q24` was the independent signal (adjusted beta -0.1041, p approximately 1e-300); `myc_amplification` and `rnaseq_MYC_log2_tpm` were not independently negative once continuous 8q24 copy number was modeled.
+
+`dependency_POLR2A` and `dependency_TMED10` were dominated by growth and screen covariates rather than a sharply defined molecular subgroup. Higher `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` strongly predicted more negative `dependency_POLR2A` (adjusted beta -0.3053, p approximately 1e-300) and more negative `dependency_TMED10` (adjusted beta -0.1010, p approximately 1e-300). `cas9_activity_score` was also negative in the TMED10 model (beta -0.1035, p=1.78e-15). `nf1_loss` had a small additional TMED10 association (beta -0.0134, p=0.013), but it was much weaker than the growth/Cas9 effects.
+
+The systematic heterogeneity search covered every dependency outcome using binary predicates, categorical levels, upper/lower quartiles of continuous variables, and pair/triple subgroup intersections. Final best-supported subgroup definitions are: BRAF: `braf_v600e=1`; EGFR: `egfr_amplification=1`; ERBB2: `erbb2_amplification=1`; KRAS: `kras_mutation=1`; RIT1: `nf1_loss=1`; KIF18A: `lineage=colorectal`, `apc_mutation=1`, high `wnt_activity_score`, and `smad4_loss=0`; TMED10: primarily high `growth_rate_doublings_per_day` with a small `nf1_loss` component; DHX9: high `rnaseq_MYC_log2_tpm`; POLR2A: high `growth_rate_doublings_per_day`; RPL11: high `copy_number_8q24`, especially overlapping `myc_amplification`, with continuous 8q24 copy number carrying the independent effect.
diff --git a/example_data_depmap/tasks/depmap/named/analysis_work.js b/example_data_depmap/tasks/depmap/named/analysis_work.js
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..d6f4fc844e21c89eb73dd53b93b4a4b2b8cf86ba
--- /dev/null
+++ b/example_data_depmap/tasks/depmap/named/analysis_work.js
@@ -0,0 +1,982 @@
+const fs = require('fs');
+
+const file = 'dataset.parquet';
+const buf = fs.readFileSync(file);
+if (buf.slice(0, 4).toString() !== 'PAR1' || buf.slice(buf.length - 4).toString() !== 'PAR1') {
+  throw new Error('Not a Parquet file');
+}
+
+const footerLen = buf.readUInt32LE(buf.length - 8);
+const footer = buf.slice(buf.length - 8 - footerLen, buf.length - 8);
+
+const CT = {
+  STOP: 0,
+  TRUE: 1,
+  FALSE: 2,
+  BYTE: 3,
+  I16: 4,
+  I32: 5,
+  I64: 6,
+  DOUBLE: 7,
+  BINARY: 8,
+  LIST: 9,
+  SET: 10,
+  MAP: 11,
+  STRUCT: 12,
+  FLOAT: 13,
+};
+
+class Reader {
+  constructor(b) {
+    this.b = b;
+    this.o = 0;
+  }
+  u8() {
+    return this.b[this.o++];
+  }
+  varintBig() {
+    let shift = 0n;
+    let out = 0n;
+    while (true) {
+      const x = BigInt(this.u8());
+      out |= (x & 0x7fn) << shift;
+      if ((x & 0x80n) === 0n) return out;
+      shift += 7n;
+    }
+  }
+  varint() {
+    return Number(this.varintBig());
+  }
+  zigzag() {
+    const n = this.varintBig();
+    const val = (n >> 1n) ^ (-(n & 1n));
+    return Number(val);
+  }
+  binary() {
+    const n = this.varint();
+    const s = this.b.slice(this.o, this.o + n);
+    this.o += n;
+    return s;
+  }
+  string() {
+    return this.binary().toString('utf8');
+  }
+  double() {
+    const x = this.b.readDoubleLE(this.o);
+    this.o += 8;
+    return x;
+  }
+  float() {
+    const x = this.b.readFloatLE(this.o);
+    this.o += 4;
+    return x;
+  }
+  field(last) {
+    const h = this.u8();
+    const type = h & 0x0f;
+    if (type === CT.STOP) return { type };
+    const delta = h >> 4;
+    let id;
+    if (delta === 0) id = this.zigzag();
+    else id = last + delta;
+    return { type, id };
+  }
+  listBegin() {
+    const h = this.u8();
+    let size = h >> 4;
+    const etype = h & 0x0f;
+    if (size === 15) size = this.varint();
+    return { size, etype };
+  }
+  skip(type) {
+    if (type === CT.TRUE || type === CT.FALSE) return;
+    if (type === CT.BYTE) {
+      this.u8();
+    } else if (type === CT.I16 || type === CT.I32 || type === CT.I64) {
+      this.zigzag();
+    } else if (type === CT.DOUBLE) {
+      this.o += 8;
+    } else if (type === CT.FLOAT) {
+      this.o += 4;
+    } else if (type === CT.BINARY) {
+      this.binary();
+    } else if (type === CT.LIST || type === CT.SET) {
+      const { size, etype } = this.listBegin();
+      for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) this.skip(etype);
+    } else if (type === CT.MAP) {
+      const size = this.varint();
+      if (size > 0) {
+        const types = this.u8();
+        const ktype = types >> 4;
+        const vtype = types & 0x0f;
+        for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) {
+          this.skip(ktype);
+          this.skip(vtype);
+        }
+      }
+    } else if (type === CT.STRUCT) {
+      let last = 0;
+      while (true) {
+        const f = this.field(last);
+        if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+        last = f.id;
+        this.skip(f.type);
+      }
+    } else {
+      throw new Error(`Unknown compact type ${type} at ${this.o}`);
+    }
+  }
+}
+
+function readList(r, fn) {
+  const { size, etype } = r.listBegin();
+  const out = [];
+  for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) out.push(fn(r, etype));
+  return out;
+}
+
+function parseSchemaElement(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.type = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.type_length = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.repetition_type = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 4) x.name = r.string();
+    else if (f.id === 5) x.num_children = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 6) x.converted_type = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 7) x.scale = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 8) x.precision = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 9) x.field_id = r.zigzag();
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+function parseColumnMetaData(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.type = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.encodings = readList(r, rr => rr.zigzag());
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.path_in_schema = readList(r, rr => rr.string());
+    else if (f.id === 4) x.codec = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 5) x.num_values = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 6) x.total_uncompressed_size = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 7) x.total_compressed_size = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 9) x.data_page_offset = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 10) x.index_page_offset = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 11) x.dictionary_page_offset = r.zigzag();
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+function parseColumnChunk(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.file_path = r.string();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.file_offset = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.meta_data = parseColumnMetaData(r);
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+function parseRowGroup(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.columns = readList(r, rr => parseColumnChunk(rr));
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.total_byte_size = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.num_rows = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 5) x.file_offset = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 6) x.total_compressed_size = r.zigzag();
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+function parseFileMetaData(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.version = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.schema = readList(r, rr => parseSchemaElement(rr));
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.num_rows = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 4) x.row_groups = readList(r, rr => parseRowGroup(rr));
+    else if (f.id === 6) x.created_by = r.string();
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+const meta = parseFileMetaData(new Reader(footer));
+const codecNames = ['UNCOMPRESSED', 'SNAPPY', 'GZIP', 'LZO', 'BROTLI', 'LZ4', 'ZSTD', 'LZ4_RAW'];
+const typeNames = ['BOOLEAN', 'INT32', 'INT64', 'INT96', 'FLOAT', 'DOUBLE', 'BYTE_ARRAY', 'FIXED_LEN_BYTE_ARRAY'];
+
+function parseDataPageHeader(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.num_values = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.encoding = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.definition_level_encoding = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 4) x.repetition_level_encoding = r.zigzag();
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+function parseDictionaryPageHeader(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.num_values = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.encoding = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.is_sorted = f.type === CT.TRUE ? true : (f.type === CT.FALSE ? false : Boolean(r.u8()));
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+function parseDataPageHeaderV2(r) {
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.num_values = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.num_nulls = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.num_rows = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 4) x.encoding = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 5) x.definition_levels_byte_length = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 6) x.repetition_levels_byte_length = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 7) x.is_compressed = f.type === CT.TRUE ? true : (f.type === CT.FALSE ? false : Boolean(r.u8()));
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  return x;
+}
+
+function parsePageHeaderAt(offset) {
+  const r = new Reader(buf.slice(offset));
+  const x = {};
+  let last = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const f = r.field(last);
+    if (f.type === CT.STOP) break;
+    last = f.id;
+    if (f.id === 1) x.type = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 2) x.uncompressed_page_size = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 3) x.compressed_page_size = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 4) x.crc = r.zigzag();
+    else if (f.id === 5) x.data_page_header = parseDataPageHeader(r);
+    else if (f.id === 7) x.dictionary_page_header = parseDictionaryPageHeader(r);
+    else if (f.id === 8) x.data_page_header_v2 = parseDataPageHeaderV2(r);
+    else r.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  x.header_size = r.o;
+  return x;
+}
+
+function snappyUncompress(input) {
+  let ip = 0;
+  let len = 0;
+  let shift = 0;
+  while (true) {
+    const b = input[ip++];
+    len |= (b & 0x7f) << shift;
+    if ((b & 0x80) === 0) break;
+    shift += 7;
+  }
+  const out = Buffer.allocUnsafe(len);
+  let op = 0;
+  while (ip < input.length) {
+    const tag = input[ip++];
+    const type = tag & 3;
+    if (type === 0) {
+      let literalLen = tag >> 2;
+      if (literalLen < 60) {
+        literalLen += 1;
+      } else {
+        const n = literalLen - 59;
+        literalLen = 0;
+        for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) literalLen |= input[ip++] << (8 * i);
+        literalLen += 1;
+      }
+      input.copy(out, op, ip, ip + literalLen);
+      ip += literalLen;
+      op += literalLen;
+    } else {
+      let copyLen, offset;
+      if (type === 1) {
+        copyLen = 4 + ((tag >> 2) & 0x7);
+        offset = ((tag & 0xe0) << 3) | input[ip++];
+      } else if (type === 2) {
+        copyLen = 1 + (tag >> 2);
+        offset = input[ip] | (input[ip + 1] << 8);
+        ip += 2;
+      } else {
+        copyLen = 1 + (tag >> 2);
+        offset = input[ip] | (input[ip + 1] << 8) | (input[ip + 2] << 16) | (input[ip + 3] << 24);
+        ip += 4;
+      }
+      for (let i = 0; i < copyLen; i++) out[op + i] = out[op - offset + i];
+      op += copyLen;
+    }
+  }
+  if (op !== len) throw new Error(`Snappy length mismatch: ${op} != ${len}`);
+  return out;
+}
+
+function readVarintAt(b, offset) {
+  let out = 0;
+  let shift = 0;
+  let o = offset;
+  while (true) {
+    const x = b[o++];
+    out |= (x & 0x7f) << shift;
+    if ((x & 0x80) === 0) return { value: out, offset: o };
+    shift += 7;
+  }
+}
+
+function readBits(b, bitPos, width) {
+  let x = 0;
+  for (let j = 0; j < width; j++) {
+    const byte = b[bitPos >> 3];
+    const bit = (byte >> (bitPos & 7)) & 1;
+    x |= bit << j;
+    bitPos++;
+  }
+  return { value: x, bitPos };
+}
+
+function decodeHybrid(b, offset, bitWidth, count) {
+  const values = [];
+  let o = offset;
+  while (values.length < count) {
+    const hv = readVarintAt(b, o);
+    const header = hv.value;
+    o = hv.offset;
+    if ((header & 1) === 0) {
+      const run = header >> 1;
+      const bytes = Math.ceil(bitWidth / 8);
+      let value = 0;
+      for (let i = 0; i < bytes; i++) value |= b[o + i] << (8 * i);
+      o += bytes;
+      for (let i = 0; i < run && values.length < count; i++) values.push(value);
+    } else {
+      const groups = header >> 1;
+      let bitPos = o * 8;
+      const total = groups * 8;
+      for (let i = 0; i < total && values.length < count; i++) {
+        const rv = readBits(b, bitPos, bitWidth);
+        values.push(rv.value);
+        bitPos = rv.bitPos;
+      }
+      o = Math.ceil(bitPos / 8);
+    }
+  }
+  return { values, offset: o };
+}
+
+function decodePlain(b, type, count) {
+  const out = [];
+  let o = 0;
+  for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
+    if (type === 5) {
+      out.push(b.readDoubleLE(o));
+      o += 8;
+    } else if (type === 2) {
+      out.push(Number(b.readBigInt64LE(o)));
+      o += 8;
+    } else if (type === 1) {
+      out.push(b.readInt32LE(o));
+      o += 4;
+    } else if (type === 6) {
+      const n = b.readInt32LE(o);
+      o += 4;
+      out.push(b.slice(o, o + n).toString('utf8'));
+      o += n;
+    } else {
+      throw new Error(`Unsupported plain type ${type}`);
+    }
+  }
+  return out;
+}
+
+function getPagePayload(pos, ph, codec) {
+  const start = pos + ph.header_size;
+  const compressed = buf.slice(start, start + ph.compressed_page_size);
+  let payload;
+  if (codec === 0) payload = compressed;
+  else if (codec === 1) payload = snappyUncompress(compressed);
+  else throw new Error(`Unsupported codec ${codec}`);
+  return { payload, next: start + ph.compressed_page_size };
+}
+
+function decodeColumn(col) {
+  const md = col.meta_data;
+  let pos = md.dictionary_page_offset ?? md.data_page_offset;
+  const end = pos + md.total_compressed_size;
+  let dictionary = null;
+  const values = [];
+  while (values.length < md.num_values && pos < end) {
+    const ph = parsePageHeaderAt(pos);
+    const { payload, next } = getPagePayload(pos, ph, md.codec);
+    pos = next;
+    if (ph.type === 2) {
+      dictionary = decodePlain(payload, md.type, ph.dictionary_page_header.num_values);
+    } else if (ph.type === 0) {
+      const h = ph.data_page_header;
+      let o = 0;
+      const defLen = payload.readInt32LE(o);
+      o += 4;
+      const def = decodeHybrid(payload.slice(o, o + defLen), 0, 1, h.num_values);
+      o += defLen;
+      const nonNull = def.values.reduce((a, x) => a + (x > 0 ? 1 : 0), 0);
+      let decoded;
+      if (h.encoding === 8 || h.encoding === 2) {
+        const bitWidth = payload[o++];
+        const ids = decodeHybrid(payload, o, bitWidth, nonNull);
+        o = ids.offset;
+        if (!dictionary) throw new Error(`Missing dictionary for ${md.path_in_schema.join('.')}`);
